 2020 expansion draft occurred on February 12 for the [[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club]] to build their initial roster.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/expansion-draft-resultts|title=2020 Expansion Draft Results|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref> The original 6 Lacrosse Clubs submitted a roster of 11 protected players (1 goalie and 10 positional players) to the PLL. These 11 players were not be available for selection by the seventh Lacrosse Club in the Expansion Draft. Any player, with the exception of active military members and rookie holdouts, not protected by their club was entered into the pool for selection by the Waterdogs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/premier-lacrosse-league-provides-details-on-expansion-draft|title=PREMIER LACROSSE LEAGUE PROVIDES DETAILS ON EXPANSION DRAFT|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Format:'''\n\n* A total of 18 players were selected in the expansion draft\n* No more than 4 players could be drafted from an existing Lacrosse Club\n* Remaining non-protected players were removed from the expansion draft pool and returned to their original club\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Pick #\n!Player\n!Pos.\n!PLL Team\n!College\n|-\n|1\n|Connor Kelly \n|Midfield\n|Whipsnakes\n|Maryland\n|-\n|2\n|Christian Cuccinello\n|Attack\n|Archers\n|Villanova\n|-\n|3\n|Brodie Merrill\n|Defense\n|Chaos\n|Georgetown\n|-\n|4\n|Charlie Cipriano\n|Goalie\n|Chaos\n|Fairfield\n|-\n|5\n|Ben Reeves\n|Attack\n|Whipsnakes\n|Yale\n|-\n|6\n|Kyle McClancy\n|Midfield\n|Chaos\n|SUNY Albany\n|-\n|7\n|Kieran McArdle\n|Attack\n|Atlas\n|St. John's\n|-\n|8\n|Brian Karalunas \n|Defense\n|Redwoods\n|Villanova\n|-\n|9\n|Ben McIntosh\n|Midfield\n|Archers\n|Drexel\n|-\n|10\n|Drew Snider\n|Midfield\n|Whipsnakes\n|Maryland\n|-\n|11\n|Ryan Drenner\n|Attack\n|Whipsnakes\n|Towson\n|-\n|12\n|Noah Richard\n|LSM\n|Atlas\n|Marquette\n|-\n|13\n|Steven DeNapoli\n|Midfield\n|Atlas\n|Hofstra\n|-\n|14\n|Wes Berg\n|Midfield\n|Redwoods\n|Denver\n|-\n|15\n|Chris Sabia\n|Defense\n|Chrome\n|Penn State\n|-\n|16\n|Ryan Conrad\n|Midfield\n|Atlas\n|Virginia\n|-\n|17\n|Dan Eipp\n|Midfield\n|Archers\n|Harvard\n|-\n|18\n|Drew Simoneau\n|Faceoff\n|Chrome\n|Nazareth College\n|}\n\n== Player Entry Draft ==\n\nThe 2020 player entry draft occurred on March 16 for teams to select players arriving from rival Major League Lacrosse. On March 4, [[Paul Burmeister]] and [[NBCSN]] hosted an entry draft lottery for selection order.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/premier-lacrosse-league-entry-draft-lottery-order-revealed|title=PREMIER LACROSSE LEAGUE ENTRY DRAFT LOTTERY ORDER REVEALED|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref> Out of 100 balls to select from, Waterdogs had 40, Chrome had 25, Atlas had 15, Archers had 10, Chaos had 6, Redwoods had 3, and the champion Whipsnakes had 1. \n\n[[Rob Pannell]] was announced to be transferring to the PLL on March 9, followed by 15 other players the following day, which comprised the selection pool for the entry draft.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=PremierLacrosse|number=1237015372416421891|title=Welcome to the PLL, @RobPannell3pic.twitter.com/4sni8W1WCe|last=League|first=Premier Lacrosse|date=2020-03-09|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=PremierLacrosse|number=1237395254866673664|title=We\u2019re excited to welcome 16 new players to the PLL who will be available during the 2020 Entry Draft!pic.twitter.com/r6VXhrqBQ9|last=League|first=Premier Lacrosse|date=2020-03-10|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> A total of 14 players were selected in the entry draft with remaining new players entering the league player pool. \n\n==== Results:<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=PremierLacrosse|number=1239686215214845952|title=The official results from the 2020 Entry Draft! #PLLEntryDraftpic.twitter.com/TY5PxGmzEF|last=League|first=Premier Lacrosse|date=2020-03-16|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rnd.\n!Pick #\n!PLL Team\n!Player\n!Pos.\n!College\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|1\n|Waterdogs\n|Zach Currier\n|Midfield\n|[[Princeton Tigers men's lacrosse|Princeton]]\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|2\n|Chrome\n|Jesse Bernhardt\n|Long Stick Midfield\n|[[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland]]\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|3\n|Atlas\n|[[Rob Pannell]]\n|Attack\n|[[Cornell Big Red men's lacrosse|Cornell]]\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|4\n|Archers\n|Eli Gobrecht\n|Defense\n|[[Ithaca College|Ithaca]]\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|5\n|Whipsnakes\n|Zed Williams\n|Midfield\n|[[Virginia Cavaliers men's lacrosse|Virginia]]\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|6\n|Redwoods\n|Finn Sullivan\n|Defense\n|[[Hofstra Pride men's lacrosse|Hofstra]]\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|7\n|Chaos\n|[[Dillon Ward]]\n|Goalie\n|[[Bellarmine University|Bellarmine]]\n|-\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|8\n|Waterdogs\n|Ryland Rees\n|Long Stick Midfield\n|[[Stony Brook Seawolves men's lacrosse|Stony Brook]]\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|9\n|Chrome\n|Donny Moss\n|Defense\n|[[Adelphi University|Adelphi]]\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|10\n|Atlas\n|Craig Chick\n|Defense\n|[[Lehigh Mountain Hawks men's lacrosse|Lehigh]]\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|11\n|Archers\n|Christian Mazzone\n|Midfield\n|[[Rutgers Scarlet Knights men's lacrosse|Rutgers]]\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|12\n|Whipsnakes\n|TJ Comizio\n|Midfield\n|[[Villanova Wildcats men's lacrosse|Villanova]]\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|13\n|Redwoods\n|Greg Puskuldjian\n|Faceoff\n|Adelphi\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|14\n|Chaos\n|Jason Noble\n|Midfield\n|Cornell\n|-\n|}\n\n== College Draft ==\nThe 2020 collegiate draft will occur on April 21 and be broadcast on [[NBCSN]]. The draft order has been set by way of the 2019 Premier Lacrosse League playoff and first draft pick brackets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/other/story/fix-tanking-playoffs-tournament-premier-lacrosse-league-how-081519|title=Has this upstart league come up with the best playoff format yet?|website=foxsports.com}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://prolacrossetalk.com/andy-copelan-discusses-choosing-the-first-18-waterdogs/|title=Andy Copelan discusses choosing the first 18 Waterdogs, who he\u2019d take at 19 and what happens next|website=prolacrosse.com}}</ref> The first draft pick game winner [[Archers Lacrosse Club | Archers]] will have the first overall pick, while the league champion [[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club | Whipsnakes]] will have the last pick in the first round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/rambo-leads-whipsnakes-to-dramatic-pll-championship-victory|title=RAMBO LEADS WHIPSNAKES TO DRAMATIC PLL CHAMPIONSHIP VICTORY|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Format:'''\n\n* Each club is awarded four picks.\n* The draft order was set from postseason play\n* Eligible players must currently be in their senior season.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rnd.\n!Pick #\n!PLL Team\n!Player\n!Pos.\n!College\n!Conference\n!Notes\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|1\n|[[Archers Lacrosse Club|Archers]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|2\n|[[Atlas Lacrosse Club|Atlas]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|3\n|[[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club|Waterdogs]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|4\n|[[Chrome Lacrosse Club|Chrome]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|5\n|[[Chaos Lacrosse Club|Chaos]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|6\n|[[Redwoods Lacrosse Club|Redwoods]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1'''\n|7\n|[[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club|Whipsnakes]] \n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|8\n|[[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club|Waterdogs]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|9\n|[[Chrome Lacrosse Club|Chrome]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|10\n|[[Atlas Lacrosse Club|Atlas]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|11\n|[[Archers Lacrosse Club|Archers]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|12\n|[[Chaos Lacrosse Club|Chaos]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|13\n|[[Chaos Lacrosse Club|Chaos]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|From Redwoods<ref>{{cite web|url=https://premierlacrosseleague.com/breaking-news-myles-jones-traded-to-redwoods-lc/|title=Breaking News: Myles Jones Traded to Redwoods LC|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''2'''\n|14\n|[[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club|Whipsnakes]] \n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|15\n|[[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club|Waterdogs]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|16\n|[[Chrome Lacrosse Club|Chrome]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|17\n|[[Chrome Lacrosse Club|Chrome]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|From Atlas\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|18\n|[[Archers Lacrosse Club|Archers]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|19\n|[[Chaos Lacrosse Club|Chaos]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|20\n|[[Atlas Lacrosse Club|Atlas]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|From Redwoods via Chrome\n|-\n|'''3'''\n|21\n|[[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club|Whipsnakes]] \n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|22\n|[[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club|Waterdogs]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|23\n|[[Chrome Lacrosse Club|Chrome]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|24\n|[[Atlas Lacrosse Club|Atlas]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|25\n|[[Redwoods Lacrosse Club|Redwoods]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|From Archers via Chrome\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|26\n|[[Chaos Lacrosse Club|Chaos]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|27\n|[[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club|Whipsnakes]] \n|\n|\n|\n|\n|From Redwoods<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidelacrosse.com/article/pll-announces-trade-window-heningburg-dealt-to-redwoods/54866|title=PLL Announces Trade Window; Heningburg Dealt to Redwoods|website=insidelacrosse.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''4'''\n|28\n|[[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club|Whipsnakes]] \n|\n|\n|\n|\n|From Whipsnakes via Archers\n|}\n\n== All Star Game ==\n\n{{main article|Premier Lacrosse League All-Star Game}}\n\nThe 2020 All-Star Game will take place in late July.\n\n== Championship ==\n\nThe 2020 Premier Lacrosse League Championship game will be played in late September following two previous weeks of playoff matchups.\n\n== Awards ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Award\n!Recipient\n!Team\n!Position\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[Jim Brown]] Most Valuable Player\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Eamon McEneaney]] Attackman of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Gary Gait|Gait]] [[Paul Gait|Brothers]] Midfielder of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Dave Pietramala]] Defensive Player of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Oren Lyons]] Goalie Player of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Brodie Merrill]] Long Stick Midfielder of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|PLL Rookie of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Dick Edell]] Coach of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Paul Cantabene]] Face Off Athlete of the Year\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|George Boiardi Hard Hat Award (SSDM)\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Welles Crowther]] Humanitarian Award\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Brendan Looney]] Leadership Award\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|Jimmy Regan Teammate Award\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Dave Huntley]] Sportmanship Award Award\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Premier Lacrosse League}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in lacrosse|Premier Lacrosse League]]\n[[Category:Premier Lacrosse League]]\n[[Category:2020 in American sports|Lacrosse]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Inaugural season of the Premier Lacrosse League}}\n{{Infobox sports season\n|logo=\n|logo_size=200px\n| league           = [[Premier Lacrosse League]]\n| sport            = [[Field lacrosse]]\n| no_of_teams      = 7\n| duration         = May 29 - September\n| season           = \n| MVP              = \n| MVP_link         = \n| top_scorer       = \n| top_scorer_link  =\n| playoffs         =\n| playoffs_link    =\n| conf1            =\n| conf1_link       =\n| conf1_champ      =\n| conf1_runner-up  =\n| conf2            =\n| conf2_link       =\n| conf2_champ      =\n| conf2_runner-up  =\n| finals           = \n| finals_link      = \n| finals_champ     = \n| finals_runner-up = \n| finals_MVP       = \n| finals_MVP_link  =\n| seasonslistnames = PLL\n| prevseason_link  = \n| prevseason_year  = [[2019 Premier Lacrosse League season | 2019]]\n| nextseason_link  = \n| nextseason_year  = 2021\n}}\n\nThe '''2020 Premier Lacrosse League season''' will be the second season of the [[Premier Lacrosse League]] (PLL).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/premier-lacrosse-league-to-add-seventh-team|title=PREMIER LACROSSE LEAGUE TO ADD SEVENTH TEAM|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref> The season will begin on May 29 and culminate with a championship game played in late September. The season begins with the [[Whipsnakes Lacrosse Club]] as the defending league champions and the [[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club]] joining the league as an expansion team.\n\n==Milestones and events==\n* February 27 - The league announces Ticketmaster as their Presenting Sponsor and Official Ticketing Partner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-27/premier-lacrosse-league-adds-ticketmaster-name-in-rights-deal|title=Premier Lacrosse League Adds Ticketmaster Name in Rights Deal|website=bloomberg.com}}</ref>\n\n===Coaching changes===\n*[[Atlas Lacrosse Club]] - [[Ben Rubeor]] was announced the new Atlas head coach after John Paul announced his retirement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/atlascoachingchange|title=Premier Lacrosse League Announces Atlas LC Coaching Change Ahead Of 2020 Season|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref> Rubeor joins the lacrosse club after serving as an offensive coordinator in the MLL. He played collegiately at the University of Virginia and had a seven year career at the professional level. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/ben-rubeor-named-new-head-coach-of-premier-lacrosse-leagues-atlas-lc|title=BEN RUBEOR NAMED NEW HEAD COACH OF PREMIER LACROSSE LEAGUE'S ATLAS LC|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref>\n\n*[[Chrome Lacrosse Club]] - Tim Soudan was introduced as the new Chrome head coach following legendary coach Dom Starsia's announcement that he would be transitioning to the league advisory board. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/coachingchanges|title=Premier Lacrosse League Announces Chrome LC Coaching Change For 2020 Season|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref> Soudan arrives with a distinguished professional coaching career, including winning coach of the year in the MLL in 2014. He transitioned into coaching lacrosse after a 14 year career indoor, outdoor, and on the [[World Lacrosse Championship]] stage. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/tim-soudan-announced-as-head-coach-of-premier-lacrosse-leagues-chrome-lc|title=TIM SOUDAN ANNOUNCED AS HEAD COACH OF PREMIER LACROSSE LEAGUE'S CHROME LC|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref>\n\n*[[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club]] - Andy Copelan became the Waterdogs Lacrosse Club's first head coach on January 2, 2020. He takes the reigns of an expansion franchise that will build its entire roster through an expansion draft, new player entry draft, and the collegiate draft. Copelan was hired based on his successful NCAA coaching resume. At the helm of [[Fairfield Stags men's lacrosse]], Copelan lead the team to the best team record under one head coach and was named [[Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference|MAAC]] coach of the year in 2015. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidelacrosse.com/article/premier-lacrosse-league-announces-waterdogs-lc-as-seventh-team-name/55744|title=Andy Copelan Named Head Coach of PLL's Waterdogs|website=insidelacrosse.com}}</ref>\n\n==Expansion==\nThe addition of a seventh team, the [[Waterdogs Lacrosse Club]], allows for natural bye weeks to occur for each team throughout the season. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/expansionteamannouncment|title=Premier Lacrosse League Announces Expansion Team For 2020 Season|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref>Paul Rabil first hinted at expansion in a post game interview after the 2019 Championship game. On January 1, 2020 the Premier Lacrosse League announced the Waterdogs identity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/lacrosse/2020/01/01/premier-lacrosse-league-introduces-waterdogs|title=How the PLL Developed Its First Expansion Team, Waterdogs Lacrosse Club|website=SportsIllustrated.com}}</ref> An expansion draft took place on February 12 and an entry draft will occur in March to build the new roster with veteran players<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslaxmagazine.com/pro/pll/premier-lacrosse-league-announces-waterdogs-lc-as-new-team-for-2020|title=PREMIER LACROSSE LEAGUE ANNOUNCES WATERDOGS LC AS NEW TEAM FOR 2020|website=uslaxmagazine.com}}</ref>.\n\n==Schedule==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! Week\n! Date\n! Games\n! Time ([[Eastern Time Zone|ET]])\n! Venue\n! City\n! Attendance\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1 || May 29 || TBA || 7:00 pm || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Gillette Stadium]] || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Foxborough, Massachusetts|Foxborough, MA]] ([[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]]) || rowspan=\"3\"| <!-- attendance here -->|| rowspan=\"3\" |\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/week1announcement|title=Premier Lacrosse League To Open 2020 Season At Gillette Stadium In Foxborough, MA|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|May 30 || TBA || 4:00 pm\n|-\n| TBA || 6:45 pm\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2 || rowspan=\"2\"|June 6 || TBA || 5:15 pm || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Fifth Third Bank Stadium]] || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Kennesaw, Georgia|Kennesaw, GA]] ([[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]]) || rowspan=\"3\"| <!-- attendance here -->|| rowspan=\"3\"|\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/atlanta2020announcment|title=Premier Lacrosse League To Return To Atlanta For 2020 Season|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| TBA || 8:00 pm\n|-\n| June 7 || TBA || 2:00 pm\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|3 || rowspan=\"1\"|June 12 || TBA || 7:00 pm || rowspan=\"3\" |[[Kenneth P. LaValle Stadium]] || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Stony Brook, New York|Stony Brook, NY]] || rowspan=\"3\"| <!-- attendance here -->|| rowspan=\"3\"|\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierlacrosseleague.com/article/stonybrookannouncment|title=Premier Lacrosse League To Host Week Three At Stony Brook University|website=premierlacrosseleague.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|June 13 || TBA || 4:00 pm\n|-\n| TBA || 6:30 pm\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|4 || rowspan=\"2\"|June 20 || TBA || 5:15 pm || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Homewood Field]] || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Baltimore, Maryland|Baltimore, MD]] || rowspan