ed States|President]] [[Bill Clinton]] easily won the primary, facing only minor opposition. \n\n== Results ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:right;\"\n|+ style=\"background-color:#f2f2f2;margin-bottom:-1px;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em 0.4em;\" |1996 New Hampshire Democratic Primary<ref>{{cite web |last1=Winger |first1=Richard |title=Ballot Access News -- March 6, 1996 |url=https://transition.fec.gov/pubrec/fe1996/presprim.htm#nh|website=Ballot Access News |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" |Candidate\n!Votes\n!%\n|-\n|- {{party shading/Democratic}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |'''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n|'''76,797'''\n|'''84.37%'''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Pat Buchanan]] \u2020\n|3,347 \n|3.68%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lamar Alexander]] \u2020 \n|1,888 \n|2.07%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Steve Forbes]] \u2020 \n|1,294\n|1.42%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Bob Dole]] \u2020 \n|1,257\n|1.38%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Pat Paulsen]] \n|1,007\n|1.11%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Al Gore]] \u2020 \n|1,257\n|0.74%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Carmen C. Chimento\n|656\n|0.72%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lyndon LaRouche]] \n|433\n|0.48%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Richard Lugar]] \u2020\n|410\n|0.45%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Caroline Killeen \n|391\n|0.43%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Heather Anne Harder\n|369\n|0.40%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Bruce Daniels\n|312\n|0.34%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |James Griffin\n|307\n|0.34%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Alan Keyes]] \u2020\n|281\n|0.31%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Collin Powell]] \u2020\n|280\n|0.31%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Ralph Nader]] \u2020\n|187\n|0.20%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Morry Taylor]] \u2020\n|167\n|0.18%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Stephen Michael\n|94\n|0.10%\n|-\n| style=\"te